41:31.766 --> 41:36.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JUDY WOODRUFF: Next: a new
take on a literary classic.

41:42.833 --> 41:45.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Jeffrey Brown has the
newest addition to the
"NewsHour" Bookshelf.

41:45.666 --> 41:50.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: A king
sacrifices his own daughter
to appease the gods.

41:50.133 --> 41:52.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
His wife takes revenge
by killing her husband.

41:52.700 --> 41:57.700 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
The story of King Agamemnon,
Queen Clytemnestra and
their children, set
against the backdrop

41:59.300 --> 42:01.966 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
of the Trojan War, is
quite literally the
stuff of Greek tragedy.

42:01.966 --> 42:06.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And now comes a new telling in
"House of Names," a novel by
one of today's leading writers,

42:07.733 --> 42:09.766 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Colm Toibin.

42:09.766 --> 42:13.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
His acclaimed books include
"The Master," "Nora Webster,"
and "Brooklyn," which was

42:13.500 --> 42:15.900 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
made into a film in 2015.

42:15.900 --> 42:17.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Welcome to you.

42:17.333 --> 42:18.766 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
COLM TOIBIN, Author, "House
of Names": Thank you.

42:18.766 --> 42:19.633 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: So, what is
this, a retelling, a rethinking?

42:19.633 --> 42:20.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
What are you doing here?

42:20.900 --> 42:22.933 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
COLM TOIBIN: Yes, it's a
retelling of the story.

42:22.933 --> 42:27.933 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And this is the great
story of war within a
family, of a family at war.

42:28.666 --> 42:30.666 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
It's an intimate war.

42:30.666 --> 42:34.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, as, for example, the war
in Syria is going on, if you
want some version of that as to

42:36.333 --> 42:40.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
a sort of myth, a sense of
how -- what it looks like when
this happens intimately, rather

42:42.966 --> 42:46.633 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
than, say, one country at war
with another, then I thought,
this is the great story, this

42:47.766 --> 42:49.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
is the myth of origin
of all civil wars.

42:49.866 --> 42:54.466 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: But it is, as
you say, at heart, a family
drama, a family tragedy.

42:56.466 --> 43:01.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Does it feel -- I have read
others of your books that are
set in an Ireland that you

43:02.800 --> 43:04.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
know or that you might have
lived -- that you have lived in.

43:04.566 --> 43:09.566 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Did it feel like these
characters were as alive
as you as those, others?

43:10.366 --> 43:12.466 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLM TOIBIN: Yes.

43:12.466 --> 43:15.600 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Once you start working with
a family, you're working with
two sorts of feeling, which is

43:15.600 --> 43:17.333 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
elemental love.

43:17.333 --> 43:22.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
But if that goes wrong,
you get rage and hatred
on a new sort of level.

43:24.066 --> 43:27.233 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I suppose I was
attempting to use a
contemporary novelist system.

43:27.233 --> 43:31.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, it is set in ancient
Greece, but, psychologically,
trying to establish, why

43:31.833 --> 43:33.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
would a woman
murder her husband?

43:33.866 --> 43:35.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She's not a psychopath.

43:35.300 --> 43:36.900 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But she's got very good
reasons to murder her husband.

43:36.900 --> 43:38.333 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

43:38.333 --> 43:40.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
COLM TOIBIN: I mean, he's
behaved atrociously toward her.

43:40.366 --> 43:45.066 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But much harder for one
to imagine how would a
son murder his own mother.

43:47.100 --> 43:50.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so I was -- yes, I became
absolutely involved, as though I
knew them, as though I could see

43:53.533 --> 43:58.533 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
everything they did, working
in detail all the time with
each of them and their motives

44:00.000 --> 44:01.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
and their shifting motives
and the rage they felt.

44:01.566 --> 44:03.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But they were also eating
together in the evening.

44:03.800 --> 44:07.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
I mean, when Orestes comes
home, his mother, like any
mother, says, oh, my God, I hope

44:07.500 --> 44:09.133 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
your bedroom is OK for you.

44:09.133 --> 44:11.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes, the little
details of everyday life.

44:11.266 --> 44:13.300 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLM TOIBIN: Yes.

44:13.300 --> 44:16.733 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And his sisters hugging him,
but actually what they all
have in mind is, where are the

44:16.733 --> 44:17.833 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
weapons?

44:17.833 --> 44:19.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What are they
eventually going to do?

44:19.900 --> 44:24.633 align:left position:12.5%,start line:73.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: You told
this in alternating
voices, but especially
the voice, the woman's

44:26.333 --> 44:31.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
voice, Clytemnestra, in a
first person, right, I, I, I?

44:31.166 --> 44:33.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLM TOIBIN: Yes.

44:33.200 --> 44:37.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
There's a late play by Euripides
called "Iphigenia in Aulis,"
which tells the story from her

44:38.033 --> 44:39.300 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
point of view.

44:39.300 --> 44:42.200 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
She was lured to the camp.

44:42.200 --> 44:44.200 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Her husband said there
was going to be a wedding.

44:44.200 --> 44:47.500 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But, in fact, they were going
to sacrifice her daughter.

44:47.500 --> 44:52.500 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So that I wanted to open it
with her, with her voice saying,
I have been acquainted with

44:53.233 --> 44:54.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
the smell of death.

44:54.200 --> 44:55.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
(CROSSTALK)

44:55.633 --> 44:56.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: That's
literally the opening line.

44:56.800 --> 44:58.866 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
COLM TOIBIN: Yes,
that's the opening line.

44:58.866 --> 45:00.433 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And it's meant to be -- it's
meant to describe how she took a
lover, so she could get someone

45:00.433 --> 45:02.400 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
to help her.

45:02.400 --> 45:05.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And she planned everything down
-- so this is a novel, also,
besides about family, it's

45:05.966 --> 45:08.466 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
about power.

45:08.466 --> 45:11.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And so anyone who is
ever seeking power should
read this book, because
it gives you a look

45:13.400 --> 45:15.366 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
into how much planning you have
to do for that single moment.

45:15.366 --> 45:18.566 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
If you get one thing wrong,
everything goes wrong.

45:18.566 --> 45:22.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And so she plans to kill
her husband when he returns
victorious from the Trojan War.

45:22.900 --> 45:27.900 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: From the
beginning in ancient times to
now, these stories are about the

45:27.900 --> 45:30.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
cycle of violence, right?

45:30.033 --> 45:34.566 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And I know that in the plays
and in Greek times, they're
looking back at, how did it

45:34.566 --> 45:35.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
all begin, right?

45:35.900 --> 45:37.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
What led to one
death after another?

45:37.900 --> 45:40.833 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But it also raises the question
of how does it ever end, right?

45:40.833 --> 45:43.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLM TOIBIN: Yes.

45:43.233 --> 45:45.966 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
That with any civil
war -- for example, the
troubles in Northern
Ireland or what's happening

45:45.966 --> 45:49.200 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
in Syria -- it begins
with one killing.

45:49.200 --> 45:51.800 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And then it's impossible to put
the genie back in the bottle.

45:51.800 --> 45:54.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
It's retaliation
after retaliation.

45:54.033 --> 45:59.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So, the violence within a
civil war or violence with a
gang feud is always a spiral.

46:01.866 --> 46:03.866 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
It's one and then it's five.

46:03.866 --> 46:07.266 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
And then it's something
atrocious occurs further.

46:07.266 --> 46:12.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So to that extent, we're still
living in that idea of violence
not as a single act, but

46:12.166 --> 46:14.266 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
as a cycle.

46:14.266 --> 46:18.166 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: You also have
in this, as in others of your
works, questions of morality,

46:18.900 --> 46:20.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
questions of religion.

46:20.733 --> 46:24.033 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
You have Queen Clytemnestra
saying that the gods
have gone, right?

46:24.033 --> 46:26.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
But we're living in a new age.

46:26.033 --> 46:28.666 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
COLM TOIBIN: It's very
hard to put the gods into
a contemporary novel.

46:28.666 --> 46:32.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So I had early on in the book
I had Clytemnestra as different
from the others, because she

46:32.700 --> 46:35.766 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
doesn't pray to the gods
or appeal to the gods.

46:35.766 --> 46:37.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
She has will.

46:37.033 --> 46:39.033 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
She makes the decisions.

46:39.033 --> 46:43.133 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
So what I wanted to do was move
it away from the godly into
the idea of it's people who

46:44.000 --> 46:46.033 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
cause this, not the gods.

46:46.033 --> 46:50.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
These killings are done by
people who decide to do them as
people, rather than having this

46:51.566 --> 46:53.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
almighty power.

46:53.633 --> 46:55.800 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: Just ask you one
general question about writing,
because I saw where you said

46:55.800 --> 47:00.833 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
once that a novel really begins
for you in a sentence, that
a sentence somehow -- and

47:02.366 --> 47:05.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
this is the quote I
saw -- contains the
full weight of a novel.

47:05.233 --> 47:06.233 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
That's an interesting idea.

47:06.233 --> 47:07.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLM TOIBIN: Yes.

47:07.500 --> 47:10.100 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
You have something on
one side of your head.

47:10.100 --> 47:13.500 align:left position:0%,start line:73.33% size:100%
And I don't know if --
I'm not a brain surgeon,
but one side of your head
might store information

47:14.633 --> 47:17.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
or an idea or a
memory or something.

47:17.266 --> 47:20.733 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And that moves of its
own accord into rhythm.

47:20.733 --> 47:25.400 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
And you get a line, that
line, I have been acquainted
with the smell of death.

47:25.400 --> 47:29.600 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
And once you get that,
you can then work.

47:29.600 --> 47:31.500 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
Until you get it, you can't.

47:31.500 --> 47:33.000 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
And so you wait for it.

47:33.000 --> 47:35.033 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
But once it's there, there's no
point in waiting for it again.

47:35.033 --> 47:36.033 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
You must work.

47:36.033 --> 47:37.500 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
JEFFREY BROWN: Yes.

47:37.500 --> 47:39.433 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
Then the work comes of
actually writing the book.

47:39.433 --> 47:40.433 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Right?

47:40.433 --> 47:41.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
COLM TOIBIN: Yes.

47:41.433 --> 47:42.966 align:left position:37.5%,start line:93.33% size:62.5%
Yes.

47:42.966 --> 47:44.166 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
JEFFREY BROWN: All right, the
new novel is "House of Names."

47:44.166 --> 47:44.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
Colm Toibin, thank
you very much.

47:44.833 --> 47:45.633 align:left position:25%,start line:93.33% size:75%
Thanks, Jeff.

47:45.633 --> 47:49.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
Thank you very much.

47:49.700 --> 47:54.700 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
JUDY WOODRUFF: And
now a story about the
founding of our nation.

47:59.266 --> 48:04.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
A distant ancestor of Rohulamin
Quander was enslaved at George
Washington's Mount Vernon

48:05.166 --> 48:07.233 align:left position:12.5%,start line:93.33% size:87.5%
estate in Virginia.

48:07.233 --> 48:11.966 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Quander is now a tour guide
there, where he offers a unique
perspective on the contributions

48:13.133 --> 48:15.266 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
of African-Americans to
our country's history.

48:15.266 --> 48:20.266 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
This story was filmed, edited
and produced by middle and
high school students who are

48:21.600 --> 48:23.666 align:left position:0%,start line:86.67% size:100%
part of the "NewsHour"'s
Student Reporting Labs program.

48:23.666 --> 48:28.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
ROHULAMIN QUANDER, Family
Historian: The past always
has an impact on the future.

48:29.966 --> 48:33.900 align:left position:12.5%,start line:80% size:87.5%
Those who do not know
their past are kind of
destined to repeat it.

48:33.900 --> 48:35.633 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
We have that program every year.

48:35.633 --> 48:37.833 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I have been coming
here all my life.

48:37.833 --> 48:40.433 align:left position:12.5%,start line:86.67% size:87.5%
I remember when I was
like about 12 years old.

48:40.433 --> 48:45.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
But I didn't fully understand
or appreciate the family's
longstanding connection.

48:45.300 --> 48:48.700 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
