when George Washington
made provisions in his
will to free his slaves.

49:17.300 --> 49:22.300 align:left position:0%,start line:80% size:100%
Her mother, Suckey Bay was her
name, was an enslaved woman who
lived on one of Washington's

49:23.166 --> 49:25.700 align:left position:0%,start line:93.33% size:100%
